What is a mental disorder?
What is a mental disorder?
A clinically significant behavioral or 
psychological syndrome or pattern that 
occurs in a person and that is associated with 
present distress (a painful symptom) or 
disability (impairment in one or more 
important areas of functioning) or with a 
significantly increased risk of suffering death, 
pain, disability, or an important loss of 
freedom. (DSM-IV)

