SCHIZOPHRENIA
SCHIZOPHRENIA
Bleuler 1911 - splitting of mental functions - disintegration of emotions, thought, and 
actions

Prevalence
1% of worldwide population - another 2-3% have schizotypal personality disorder
•
no great geographical variation
•
slight tendency for birth in winter or spring (virus?)
•

Syndrome
Psychosis – alteration in thoughts, perceptions, consciousness
•
Thought disorder - disconnected, loose thoughts
•
• Abnormal beliefs or delusions 
– persecution, reference, control,
– possession of thought
• Abnormal experiences/perceptions
– auditory hallucinations
• Mood disorders - depression, anxiety
• Motor alterations - restlessness, purposeless overactivity
Social function - withdrawal
•
• Negative - poverty of speech, poor attention span, flat affect, lack of motivation
Positive - delusions, hallucinations, bizarre or disorganized behaviors
•
• Catatonia - mutism, abnormal posture
Paranoia - persecution
•

