Hereditary Influences - Monozygotic twin concordance = 
50%; dizygotic = 15% (same as siblings)

•

lifetime probability is 10% in first-degree relatives vs. 1% 
in general population
– one parent = 13%
– two parents = 50%
• concordance rate for monozygotic twins similar whether 
reared together or not
• being adopted away from relatives with schizophrenia 
does not reduce risk
• higher in urban areas; higher for moving across cultures 
(stress?)
• multifactorial polygenic-environmental threshold model

