Treatment
• neuroleptics
– block post-synaptic dopamine receptors & release of dopamine 
from presynaptic neurons
• drug is fully effective at receptors within hours but maximal clinical 
effect takes weeks and remain for weeks after treatment ends
side effects
– early on - parkinsonian symptoms (20-40%)
– later on - tardive dyskinesia (20%)
– abnormal involuntary movements - smacking lips, chewing, tongue 
protrusion
– clozapine (late 1980s) – no tardive dyskinesia, but other risks 
including live function, reduction in white cells, must be 
monitored, expensive
– behavioral therapy can enhance drug efficacy

Dopamine theory of schizophrenia
antipsychotics
